radiographic_examinations.findings: Absence of the uterus and cervix; clusters of simple cysts in the right adnexal region; right ovary not visualized, and cysts measured 24 mm by 25 mm and 18 mm by 17 mm on the right, and 18 mm by 17 mm and 20 mm by 21 mm on the left.
Borderline low bone mass in the spine (T score, −1.10); normal bone mass in vertebral bodies (T score, −0.20); normal bone mass in femoral neck (T score, −0.90).

radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal-length vagina; no discernible uterus or cervix; cordlike structures suggesting round ligaments; bilateral thin, linear, hyperintense tubelike structures; right and left gonads identified in the anterior pelvis without definite follicles.
